{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"[E4] rebar-ticket trailer policy for shepherded patches — confirmed + consistent with onboarding. Policy: the shepherd creates/uses a rebar ticket and amends the 'rebar-ticket:' trailer into the commit message (message-only amend; authorship untouched). Cross-checked against docs/your-first-change.md's outsider-ticket flow (open a GitHub issue -> maintainer files the rebar ticket -> id goes in the trailer): aligned — in both, the maintainer/shepherd owns ticket creation and the trailer, so the outsider never needs store write access."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783649309601574001,"uuid":"0bf83cba-cad2-4c9e-b00c-88f4b8619d13"}